data.title: Jam Oasis
data.meta_description: Need a musical rest?The Jam Oasis is a safe place to make music and friends.Join us every Monday night for open jam sessions led by four teams of volunteers with a different them each week. Great place to socialize and connect with other musicians.All levels welcome, especially beginners! This is a
data.text:
2nd Monday of each month, 7:00 - 8:30 PM

Location: Mid-City Community Music (in the small sanctuary)

4011 Ohio St. San Diego, CA 92104

Hosts: Bonnie Nicholls and George Sanger

With our chairs placed in a circle, we‚Äôll perform in the round, making it a cozy, safe place to share your musical creations. Participants are invited to play:

Original songs

Covers that you‚Äôve made into your own

Please note: This event was previously a jam. We have transitioned to a listening room format, in which every participant plays a song without accompaniment from others, unless you request it.

Please keep your songs to under 5 minutes so everyone has a chance to play twice.

Also, this song circle is acoustic except for a digital piano and bass. Charts are not provided or projected.

FREE. Suggested donation: $10.

Join Mary Jane Cupp and Paul Belke for the in-person San Diego Bluegrass Society jam

‚Äã

Fun and friendly way to learn and practice jamming skills:

Playing chordal backup & simple leads

Using a capo

Singing lead & harmony parts

Jamming etiquette

Learning bluegrass standards at slower tempos

If you are a beginning/intermediate guitar, banjo, mandolin, fiddle, dobro, or bass player (or even ukulele or dulcimer player!), of any age, you will enjoy learning & reviewing bluegrass jamming basics with other friendly folks!

Chords are represented as Roman Numerals, not letters.

‚Äã

Check out the San Diego Bluegrass Society at: www.sandiegobluegrass.org

$10 Public / $5 SDBGS Members

‚Äã

For any questions or concerns please contact Mary Jane: mjcupp@yahoo.com

Location:

Queen Bee's Art and Cultural Center, 3925 Ohio St, San Diego, CA 92104, USA

Park at the French Montessori school at 4011 Ohio st, San Diego, CA, 92104 and walk down to Queen Bee's, or get cheap parking instructions here

‚ÄãJoin us with the instrument of your choice. This jam features ukulele-oriented chords and offers opportunities to lead a song, try a different instrument, but mostly have a great time.

Songs are projected at the front of the room. Here is a link to our 3rd Monday Song Set => M2 Songs.

If you'd like to lead a song we don't have, please have your chart ready as a Google Doc and send Cadence a message at least 7 days before the meetup.

Like all Mid-City Community Music jams, it's about community, and everybody playing along. Feel free to stay in your seat or try something new! There is a $10 recommended donation.

Come jam with Jellyfish (formerly The MyKey Collective a.k.a. Team 4) which is collectively comprised of;

Mikey, Bob & Donna, BobH, Ron, Greg, George, and Katie.

Fun and friendly jam session open to all levels.

Charts will be displayed via projector and screen.

Format: First hour a.k.a. First Set -Team 4 pick. After break, participants pick from our MCCM Songbook or provide hard chart copies of their song choice.

"Participants who wish to lead a song have the option to lead it by themselves, or with help from members of Team 4 "

If you have a song that‚Äôs not in our songbook, and want to play it, please email me, Michael Evans a.k.a. Mikey at conceptualphotographer@gmail.com with a chart in the PDF format at least a week before the jam so we might include it in the second half.

Please include your name and in the Subject Line, please reference ‚ÄúMy Song Suggestion for MCCM 4th Monday Jam‚Äù.
